GUILTY plea entered to count 1, deliver Klonopin.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend sixty (60) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 12-09-14 by 6:00 p.m. (Court will reconsider changing the starting date if defendant shows proof of scheduled knee surgery)
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Pay court costs;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
8) no possession of any controlled substance unless legally prescribed to him and taken in prescribed doses;
9) no contact with any illicit drug dealers or users.
Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights.
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
Minutes.
